<DocsLayout
  title="Stats Folder Issues"
  description="Fix problems with stats folder detection."
  prevPage={{ slug: "themes", title: "Themes" }}
  nextPage={{ slug: "runs-not-appearing", title: "Runs Not Appearing" }}
>
  <h2>Stats Folder Not Detected</h2>
  <p>
    If RefleK's can't find your KovaaK's stats folder automatically, you'll need
    to set it manually.
  </p>

  <h2>Manual Configuration</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Open Settings (gear icon in the top right)</li>
    <li>Go to General → Stats Folder</li>
    <li>Enter the path to your KovaaK's stats folder</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="image-container">
    <img
      src="/assets/images/settings.webp"
      alt="RefleK's settings showing stats folder configuration"
      loading="lazy"
    />
  </div>

  <h2>Common Locations</h2>
  <p>The stats folder is typically at one of these locations:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <code
        >C:\Program Files
        (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\FPSAimTrainer\FPSAimTrainer\stats</code
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      <code
        >D:\SteamLibrary\steamapps\common\FPSAimTrainer\FPSAimTrainer\stats</code
      >
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Finding Your Stats Folder</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Open Steam</li>
    <li>Right-click on KovaaK's in your library</li>
    <li>Select "Manage" → "Browse local files"</li>
    <li>Navigate to the <code>FPSAimTrainer</code> folder inside</li>
    <li>You should see a <code>stats</code> folder</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Verify the Folder</h2>
  <p>The stats folder should contain CSV files with names like:</p>
  <p>
    <code>ScenarioName - Challenge - 2025.01.28-14.30.45 Stats.csv</code>
  </p>
  <p>If you see these files, you've found the right folder.</p>

  <div class="note">
    <strong>Still having issues?</strong> Join our <a
      href="https://discord.gg/SFsf4GQhJU"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">Discord server</a
    > for help.
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
